# ─── Python ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
build/
dist/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# Virtual environments
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/

# ─── Models, activations, artifacts (regenerable, and can be large) ───
# Trained probe + metrics — regenerate with `python -m src.probe`
artifacts/*.joblib
artifacts/*.json
# Extracted activations — regenerate with `python -m src.extract`
data/activations.npz
# Exported ONNX + sample inputs — regenerate with `python -m zkp.export_onnx_coreops`
zkp/artifacts/*.onnx
zkp/artifacts/*.npy
# Benchmark outputs
bench_results.json
*.bench.json

# ─── Cached third-party datasets (re-downloaded on first run) ─────────
# InjecAgent files fetched by data/injecagent.py
data/injecagent/
# HuggingFace / datasets cache, if it ever lands in-tree
.cache/
hf_cache/

# ─── Vendored / cloned JOLT Atlas repo (clone separately, don't commit) ─
# The zkp benchmark expects jolt-atlas checked out alongside; it is its own
# repo with its own license and a huge Rust target/ tree. Do NOT vendor it.
jolt-atlas/
/jolt-atlas

# ─── Rust build output (in case anything Rust lands here) ─────────────
target/
Cargo.lock

# ─── Secrets / local config — never commit ───────────────────────────
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key
secrets.*
**/credentials*.json
# ICME guardrail keys are read from the environment (ICME_API_KEY,
# ICME_POLICY_ID); never hard-code them into a committed file.

# ─── OS / editor cruft ───────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
.vscode/
path/to/venv/
**/site-packages/
